				\begin{document}$$\upmu$$\end{document}μg of ligated pUSEBR-CRISPR Library plasmid DNA was then electroporated into Endura electrocompetent cells (Lucigen). Competent cells were recovered for 1 h at 37 °C, plated across four 15-cm LB-Carbenicillin plates (Teknova), and incubated at 37 °C for 16 h. The total number of bacterial colonies per sub-pool was quantified using serial dilution plates, to ensure a library representation of > 10,000-fold. The next morning, bacterial colonies were scraped and briefly expanded for 4 h at 37 °C in 500 mL of LB-Carbenicillin. Plasmid DNA was isolated using the QIAfilter Plasmid Maxi Kit (Qiagen). To assess sgRNA distribution, the sgRNA target region was amplified using primers that append Illumina sequencing adapters on the 5′ and 3′ ends of the amplicon, as well as a random nucleotide stagger and unique demultiplexing barcode on the 5′ end. Library amplicons were size-selected on a 2% agarose gel, purified using the QIAquick Gel Extraction Kit (Qiagen), and sequenced on an Illumina NextSeq instrument (75nt single-end reads).

